        "title": "docs: plan native durable workflow core",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR documents the proposed native durable workflow core direction for OpenClaw.\n\nIt defines the target architecture, scope boundaries, upstream PR stack, anti-goals, and the line between a durable coordination slice and a full durable workflow engine.\n\n## Why\n\nOpenClaw has recurring long-running coordination failure modes: silent runs, gateway restart uncertainty, subagent fan-in gaps, and insufficient operator visibility. This document proposes a small local-first durable core rather than a Temporal/Restate clone.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis is PR 1 in a stacked durable core series.\n\nStack order:\n\n1. Docs and architecture plan\n2. Durable workflow kernel primitives\n3. Gateway and CLI lifecycle integration\n\n## Validation\n\nDocs-only PR.\n",
